<div class="call-section call-intro">

  <p>
    We invite submissions of poster abstracts for the IROS 2026 Workshop on Haptics and Dexterous Manipulation.
  </p>

  <p>
    The poster session will provide an informal forum where researchers can present ongoing work, emerging ideas, and recent results related to the integration of haptics, tactile sensing, and dexterous robotic manipulation.
  </p>

  <p>
    The goal of this session is to foster discussion and collaboration between researchers working on the fundamental technologies enabling human-like dexterity in robotic systems.
  </p>

</div>

<div class="call-section">
  <h2 class="section-title">Topics of Interest</h2>

  <p>
    Relevant topics for the poster session include, but are not limited to:
  </p>

  <div class="topics-box">
    <ul>
      <li>Haptic feedback for robotic manipulation</li>
      <li>Tactile sensing and perception</li>
      <li>Bio-inspired tactile systems</li>
      <li>Slip detection and tactile event sensing</li>
      <li>Dexterous robotic manipulation</li>
      <li>Control strategies for dexterous manipulation</li>
      <li>Learning-based control for manipulation</li>
      <li>Teleoperation and human-in-the-loop manipulation</li>
      <li>Human tactile perception and psychophysics</li>
      <li>Haptic interfaces and wearable haptics</li>
      <li>Machine learning for tactile sensing</li>
      <li>Applications of haptics in robotics, VR/AR, and telemanipulation</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="call-section">
  <h2 class="section-title">Submission Guidelines</h2>

  <div class="submission-box">
    <p>
      Poster submissions should include:
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li>One-page abstract in PDF format</li>
      <li>Title, authors, affiliations, and a brief description of the work</li>
      <li>Optional figures illustrating the approach or results</li>
      <li>A required graphical summary in PNG or JPG format</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      The graphical summary will be used for the poster listing on the workshop website and for the digital poster booklet distributed to workshop participants.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

